<TEXT>     The panel also found that "agents of the Chilean state" were responsible
for the <DATE>Sept. 21, 1976</DATE>, car bombing in <LOCATION>Washington</LOCATION> that killed <LOCATION>Orlando Letelier</LOCATION>
-- formerly Allende's ambassador to the <LOCATION>United States</LOCATION> -- and his assistant
<PERSON>Ronnie Moffet</PERSON>.  </TEXT>
